---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { PHOTO_ALBUM_TITLE } from "../lib/constants";
import PhotoGallery from "../components/PhotoGallery.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
	pageTitle={PHOTO_ALBUM_TITLE}
	pageDescription="Photo album featuring all photos taken by Rika on Love and Deepspace game."
/>
<div class="body-wrapper">
	<section class="hero">
		<p class="hero-eyebrow">LOVE AND DEEPSPACE</p>
		<h1 class="hero-title"><em>Rika's</em> Photo Album</h1>
		<p class="hero-sub">
			I told myself I'd never get into in-game photography. No spending
			real-life currency on outfits, backgrounds, or poses - that was one
			of my rules as a low-spender. Well... that didn't last. I saw what
			other players were creating in Glint Photobooth. One thing led to
			another, and I found myself experimenting (and caved on a few
			outfits along the way).<br /><br />
			Here's what came out of it. Clicking any photo below will take you to
			its original X post, where you'll find the full caption and whatever thoughts,
			song title or lyric I had in mind when I posted it.
		</p>
	</section>
	<PhotoGallery />
	<Footer />
</div>
